     <header>
        <h1>How To Make A Latte</h1>
        image
        <p>Nowadays espresso machines are available to buy for your home, giving you the chance to bring the coffee shop to your kitchen. Here's a simple recipe for a delicious latte using a home espresso machine. </p>
    </header>
    <section>
        <h2>Ingredients</h2>
          <ul>
            <li>Espresso coffee (fine grain)</li>
            <li>Water</li>
            <li>Milk - Dairy/Plant-based</li>
            <li>Sugar/Honey/Latte Syrup (Optional)</li>
          </ul>
    </section>
    <section>
        <h2>Preparation</h2>
          <ol>
            <li>Fill  up the espresso machine with water and turn it on to heat up.</li>
            <li>Twist the handle on the machine and remove the portafilter.</li>
            <li>Measure the correct amount of coffee and place it in the filter and tamp it down.</li>
            <li>Place a cup under the portafilter and push the button on the machine to produce the espresso shot.</li>
            <li>Fill a small jug with approximately 150 ml of your chosen milk and push the froth button on the machine.</li>
            <li>Place the nozzle into the milk and allow the machine to work its magic.</li>
            <li>Tap the jug on the counter when finished and then add to your espresso.</li>
            <li>Add sugar, honey or latte syrup to taste.</li>
            <li>Enjoy a cup of smooth latte!</li>
          </ol>
       
    </section>
